{"type":"message","id":"c57f16b8","parentId":"f16e53fa","timestamp":"2026-03-25T00:55:13.976Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-25 08:55:11 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM | 姚霖 (ou_d75c71eb9cc3369175d62f2892cd7b8b) [msg:om_x100b53076826acb0c44cb5c039e7ea0]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b53076826acb0c44cb5c039e7ea0\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_d75c71eb9cc3369175d62f2892cd7b8b\",\n  \"sender\": \"姚霖\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-25 08:55 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"姚霖 (ou_d75c71eb9cc3369175d62f2892cd7b8b)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_d75c71eb9cc3369175d62f2892cd7b8b\",\n  \"name\": \"姚霖\"\n}\n```\n\n我需要一个链接快速查看本地文件，看看有什么好的技能可以实现"}],"timestamp":1774400113973}}
{"type":"message","id":"41fff59e","parentId":"c57f16b8","timestamp":"2026-03-25T00:55:29.008Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"姚总问的是\"需要一个链接快速查看本地文件，看看有什么好的技能可以实现\"。\n\n这应该是需要找一个技能，能够通过链接快速查看本地文件。我需要先了解姚总的具体需求：\n1. 本地文件是指服务器上的文件，还是某台电脑上的文件？\n2. \"链接快速查看\"是什么意思？是需要一个web界面来浏览文件，还是一个可以在飞书/微信里打开的链接？\n\n让我先看看workspace目录下有什么技能可用，以及查找一下clawhub.com上有没有相关的技能。\n\n首先让我搜索一下相关的技能。","thinkingSignature":"76f60844240e4c29b52a20bd3814473deecd686d1c68997ccf269531b9cf072a"},{"type":"text","text":"姚总您好！\n\n根据您的需求，我来分析一下可能的实现方案：\n\n**您的需求拆解：**\n- 想通过**链接**快速查看本地文件\n- 核心目的：快速浏览/分享本地文件内容\n\n**目前有几个思路，我帮您梳理一下：**\n\n---\n\n**方案1：文件浏览Web服务**\n- 搭建一个轻量级Web文件服务器\n- 生成可分享的链接，打开后直接浏览/下载文件\n- 类似 Python 一行命令：`python3 -m http.server 8080`\n\n**方案2：内网穿透 + 文件服务**\n- 本地启动文件服务 + 内网穿透工具（如frp、nps）\n- 生成外网可访问的固定链接\n- 适合需要长期稳定访问的场景\n\n**方案3：成熟工具（推荐）**\n- **Tana** 或 **FileStash** 等自托管文件分享工具\n- 支持链接分享、预览、下载\n- 可通过浏览器直接访问\n\n---\n\n**快速确认几个问题：**\n1. 您是想在**飞书里直接点链接**打开查看？还是任何浏览器都行？\n2. 文件是在**这台服务器**上，还是**某台内网电脑**上？\n3. 需要**临时分享**还是**长期可用**的链接？\n4. 文件类型主要是**文档/图片**还是**任意文件**？\n\n您告诉我具体场景，我帮您选最合适的方案 😊"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":137,"output":402,"cacheRead":21187,"cacheWrite":35247,"totalTokens":56973,"cost":{"input":0.000041099999999999996,"output":0.00048239999999999996,"cacheRead":0.00063561,"cacheWrite":0.00422964,"total":0.0053887499999999994}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774400113974}}
{"type":"message","id":"9f0ab943","parentId":"41fff59e","timestamp":"2026-03-25T00:56:45.659Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-25 08:56:44 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM | 姚霖 (ou_d75c71eb9cc3369175d62f2892cd7b8b) [msg:om_x100b5307627a20a4c10b83b2e2545da]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5307627a20a4c10b83b2e2545da\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_d75c71eb9cc3369175d62f2892cd7b8b\",\n  \"sender\": \"姚霖\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-25 08:56 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"姚霖 (ou_d75c71eb9cc3369175d62f2892cd7b8b)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_d75c71eb9cc3369175d62f2892cd7b8b\",\n  \"name\": \"姚霖\"\n}\n```\n\n文件就是在你的本地文件，就是你经常存放文件的地方，我想在飞书里面直接查看"}],"timestamp":1774400205654}}
{"type":"message","id":"2e8b7aa4","parentId":"9f0ab943","timestamp":"2026-03-25T00:56:56.896Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"明白了，姚总的需求是：\n1. 文件在OpenClaw运行的服务器本地（就是我经常存放文件的地方，即 `/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace` 目录）\n2. 想要在飞书里直接点链接查看\n\n这其实就是需要一个文件预览/下载服务，让飞书里的链接能直接访问到本地文件。\n\n最简单的方案：\n1. 在服务器上启动一个静态文件服务\n2. 端口映射或内网穿透让外网能访问\n3. 生成飞书可以打开的链接\n\n让我先看看find-skills技能文件，看看有没有相关的技能推荐。","thinkingSignature":"e2123f0d570437f8b566bd4269c84189413dd2b12a04957b69fd0faf962524d8"},{"type":"text","text":"明白了！文件在OpenClaw的服务器本地，您想从飞书里直接点链接查看。\n\n这个需求有现成的成熟方案，我来帮您实现：\n\n**推荐方案：本地文件Web服务 + 内网穿透**\n\n让我先看看有没有现成的技能可以参考：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0qu69naof7z6_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/skills/find-skills/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":137,"output":224,"cacheRead":56166,"cacheWrite":839,"totalTokens":57366,"cost":{"input":0.000041099999999999996,"output":0.0002688,"cacheRead":0.0016849799999999998,"cacheWrite":0.00010067999999999999,"total":0.00209556}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774400205656}}
{"type":"message","id":"6ab9634d","parentId":"2e8b7aa4","timestamp":"2026-03-25T00:56:57.026Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0qu69naof7z6_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: find-skills\ndescription: Helps users discover and install agent skills when they ask questions like \"how do I do X\", \"find a skill for X\", \"is there a skill that can...\", or express interest in extending capabilities. This skill should be used when the user is looking for functionality that might exist as an installable skill.\n---\n\n# Find Skills\n\nThis skill helps you discover and install skills from the open agent skills ecosystem.\n\n## When to Use This Skill\n\nUse this skill when the user:\n\n- Asks \"how do I do X\" where X might be a common task with an existing skill\n- Says \"find a skill for X\" or \"is there a skill for X\"\n- Asks \"can you do X\" where X is a specialized capability\n- Expresses interest in extending agent capabilities\n- Wants to search for tools, templates, or workflows\n- Mentions they wish they had help with a specific domain (design, testing, deployment, etc.)\n\n## What is the Skills CLI?\n\nThe Skills CLI (`npx skills`) is the package manager for the open agent skills ecosystem. Skills are modular packages that extend agent capabilities with specialized knowledge, workflows, and tools.\n\n**Key commands:**\n\n- `npx skills find [query]` - Search for skills interactively or by keyword\n- `npx skills add <package>` - Install a skill from GitHub or other sources\n- `npx skills check` - Check for skill updates\n- `npx skills update` - Update all installed skills\n\n**Browse skills at:** https://skills.sh/\n\n## How to Help Users Find Skills\n\n### Step 1: Understand What They Need\n\nWhen a user asks for help with something, identify:\n\n1. The domain (e.g., React, testing, design, deployment)\n2. The specific task (e.g., writing tests, creating animations, reviewing PRs)\n3. Whether this is a common enough task that a skill likely exists\n\n### Step 2: Search for Skills\n\nRun the find command with a relevant query:\n\n```bash\nnpx skills find [query]\n```\n\nFor example:\n\n- User asks \"how do I make my React app faster?\" → `npx skills find react performance`\n- User asks \"can you help me with PR reviews?\" → `npx skills find pr review`\n- User asks \"I need to create a changelog\" → `npx skills find changelog`\n\nThe command will return results like:\n\n```\nInstall with npx skills add <owner/repo@skill>\n\nvercel-labs/agent-skills@vercel-react-best-practices\n└ https://skills.sh/vercel-labs/agent-skills/vercel-react-best-practices\n```\n\n### Step 3: Present Options to the User\n\nWhen you find relevant skills, present them to the user with:\n\n1. The skill name and what it does\n2. The install command they can run\n3. A link to learn more at skills.sh\n\nExample response:\n\n```\nI found a skill that might help! The \"vercel-react-best-practices\" skill provides\nReact and Next.js performance optimization guidelines from Vercel Engineering.\n\nTo install it:\nnpx skills add vercel-labs/agent-skills@vercel-react-best-practices\n\nLearn more: https://skills.sh/vercel-labs/agent-skills/vercel-react-best-practices\n```\n\n### Step 4: Offer to Install\n\nIf the user wants to proceed, you can install the skill for them:\n\n```bash\nnpx skills add <owner/repo@skill> -g -y\n```\n\nThe `-g` flag installs globally (user-level) and `-y` skips confirmation prompts.\n\n## Common Skill Categories\n\nWhen searching, consider these common categories:\n\n| Category        | Example Queries                          |\n| --------------- | ---------------------------------------- |\n| Web Development | react, nextjs, typescript, css, tailwind |\n| Testing         | testing, jest, playwright, e2e           |\n| DevOps          | deploy, docker, kubernetes, ci-cd        |\n| Documentation   | docs, readme, changelog, api-docs        |\n| Code Quality    | review, lint, refactor, best-practices   |\n| Design          | ui, ux, design-system, accessibility     |\n| Productivity    | workflow, automation, git                |\n\n## Tips for Effective Searches\n\n1. **Use specific keywords**: \"react testing\" is better than just \"testing\"\n2. **Try alternative terms**: If \"deploy\" doesn't work, try \"deployment\" or \"ci-cd\"\n3. **Check popular sources**: Many skills come from `vercel-labs/agent-skills` or `ComposioHQ/awesome-claude-skills`\n\n## When No Skills Are Found\n\nIf no relevant skills exist:\n\n1. Acknowledge that no existing skill was found\n2. Offer to help with the task directly using your general capabilities\n3. Suggest the user could create their own skill with `npx skills init`\n\nExample:\n\n```\nI searched for skills related to \"xyz\" but didn't find any matches.\nI can still help you with this task directly! Would you like me to proceed?\n\nIf this is something you do often, you could create your own skill:\nnpx skills init my-xyz-skill\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774400216965}}
{"type":"message","id":"587959d1","parentId":"6ab9634d","timestamp":"2026-03-25T00:57:01.585Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"根据find-skills技能的指导，我可以帮姚总实现这个需求。但这不是一个标准化的技能能解决的，需要自己实现。\n\n让我直接给姚总一个可行的解决方案：\n\n**最简单的方案：**\n1. 在OpenClaw服务器上启动一个轻量文件服务\n2. 使用内网穿透工具（如ngrok、frp等）让外网可访问\n3. 生成飞书可以打开的链接\n\n让我先检查一下这台服务器的环境，看看有什么工具可用。","thinkingSignature":"1325b2e71a97e5f56c35bbb76eade0c9aefc6b71c4fb709669d756fe70dae40f"},{"type":"text","text":"让我先看看服务器环境，选最适合的方案：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_78kf98oat3ps_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which python3 && which node && which npx && ls /home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2311,"output":155,"cacheRead":56166,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58632,"cost":{"input":0.0006933,"output":0.000186,"cacheRead":0.0016849799999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0025642799999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774400217026}}
